Description:
Harbour of Naples. Castel dell'Ovo (with wind mills on pier). In drawing by Jan Brueghel in Rotterdam, published by M.[Matthias] Winner, [Neubestimmtes und Unbestimmtes im zeichnerischen Werk von Jan Brueghel d. Ä.],  in JB.d.Berlin Museen [=Jahrbuch der Berliner Museen], XIV, 1972, [pp. 122-160], Abb. 4, and partly in another Boymans drawing (Winner, Abb.3). Castel dell'Ovo with windmill also in drawing (or rather fragment of a drawing in Coll. Count Seilern (Flemish Paintings and Drawings at 56 Princes Gate, Addenda, 1969, N° 320, attrib. to P.B.I. (with question mark). It may indeed be a fragment of a larger drawing, as L. Burchard suggested, and possibly another Naples view by P.B. 
Query: What date? A.S. dates 1555-60; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. nearer to 1560/61, cf. Münz 41: Sun rising over a Valley (Louvre, dated 1561).'

Keyword: Londen, Courtauld Institute of Art, Seilern Collectie
